kpal

An on-the-fly palette changer written in c, inspired by Dylan Araps' okpal [0].  


BACKGROUND
----------

This code base is non-functional at this time and will be promoted to release 
once the following features are implemented:

- [ ] Select palette
- [ ] Select random palette
- [x] List all palettes
- [x] Set light theme
- [x] Print help/usage.
- [x] Print Version
- [x] Print current palette
- [ ] save new palette to .config/


INSTALLATION
------------

From git source:

$ git clone https://github.com/mcpcpc/kpal.git
$ cd kpal/
$ make
$ make install


USAGE
-----

kpal [-s palette|-L|-r] [l|-v|-p]
-s palette  Select a palette
-l          List all palettes
-p          Print current palette
-r          Select a random palette
-L          Set light themes (modifier for -s/-r)
-h          Show this information
-v          Show version information


REFERENCES
----------
[0] https://github.com/dylanaraps/okpal
[1] https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/7908799/xsh/getopt.html
